{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"SPIKE RESOLVED (AC1). rebar's call shape is Agent(system_prompt=<parent plan>) + run_sync(<per-pairing instructions>) — instructions is the pydantic-ai user_prompt, NOT pydantic-ai 'instructions', so there are NO instruction_parts. In pydantic_ai 1.107.0 anthropic.py:1611-1616 the no-instruction-parts branch of anthropic_cache_instructions puts cache_control on cache_block_idx=0 = the system_prompt block DIRECTLY. => system-prompt caching IS supported for our shape; no instructions=/user-message CachePoint fallback needed. Implemented at the shared runner seam (runner.py): anthropic-GATED AnthropicModelSettings(anthropic_cache_instructions=True, anthropic_cache_tool_definitions=True) attached via kwargs (flows to text + structured + retry agents); gated on resolved.startswith('anthropic') so openai/gemini are unchanged. result.usage() captured via _extract_usage (RunUsage.cache_read_tokens/cache_write_tokens — pydantic-ai normalizes Anthropic's cache_read_input_tokens) and surfaced per run on result['_usage'] + the INFO log line. No RunRequest content change => structured-output retry path untouched (fidelity-neutral). Tests: gating (anthropic on / openai+gemini off), usage extraction (+defensive), wiring (settings reach Agent kwargs), container system-prompt byte-stability across children. Subagent code review: PASS (only out-of-scope NITs)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577430163295001,"uuid":"22848d0d-58fc-41f9-a0e8-bccb81aa945c"}